<i>noun</i>: 열풍 [열풍], 열병 [열병], 열기 [열기], 열 [열], 신열 [시녈], 발열 [바렬] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>열풍 [열풍]</dt><br>
<dd>1. strong wind</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 사납고 거세게 부는 바람.</dd><br>
<dd>A strong wind blowing violently.</dd><br>
<dd>2. craze; fever; fad</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 매우 거세게 일어나는 기운이나 현상.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A spirit or phenomenon rising or sweeping wildly.</dd><br>
<dt>열병 [열병]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fever</dd><br>
<dd>열이 심하게 오르는 병.</dd><br>
<dd>The disease with a high body temperature.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fever</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 어떤 일에 병적으로 흥분한 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A state of being morbidly excited about a certain thing.</dd><br>
<dt>열기 [열기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. heat; hotness</dd><br>
<dd>뜨거운 기운.</dd><br>
<dd>Hot air</dd><br>
<dd>2. feverishness</dd><br>
<dd>몸에 열이 있는 기운.</dd><br>
<dd>Fever in one's body.</dd><br>
<dd>3. excitement; enthusiasm; fever</dd><br>
<dd>흥분된 분위기.</dd><br>
<dd>An excited atmosphere.</dd><br>
<dd>4. zeal; enthusiasm; eagerness</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 하고자 하는 욕구.</dd><br>
<dd>One's desire to do something.</dd><br>
<dt>열 [열]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fever</dd><br>
<dd>아플 때 몸에 생기는 더운 기운.</dd><br>
<dd>A hot sensation that occurs when one is sick.</dd><br>
<dd>2. heat</dd><br>
<dd>뜨겁게 만드는 에너지.</dd><br>
<dd>An energy that causes something to become hot.</dd><br>
<dd>3. energy; hard work; effort</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일에 다하는 정성.</dd><br>
<dd>The devotion that one gives to something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. rage; fury; anger</dd><br>
<dd>매우 화가 나거나 흥분한 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being furious or agitated.</dd><br>
<dt>신열 [시녈]</dt><br>
<dd>fever</dd><br>
<dd>병이 나서 몸에 나는 열.</dd><br>
<dd>Fever in the body due to an illness.</dd><br>
<dt>발열 [바렬]</dt><br>
<dd>1. heating; exothermicity</dd><br>
<dd>열이 남. 또는 열을 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being heated, or the act of generating heat.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fever; febrility</dd><br>
<dd>체온이 높아짐. 또는 그런 증상.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which one's temperature becomes high or such a symptom.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>